node.text:
Visit @SculptMovements 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit! .
Treino de MMI com 01. Agachamento máquina 15/12/10 + drop com extensora 4 x 4 / 4x3 / 4x2 /4x 1 aumentando a carga ( 1 série ) 
1 x 10 com pico de contração em cima + 10 saindo da inércia 
1 x 10 com excêntrica lenta + 10 concêntrica lenta + 10 
02. Stiff 3 x 15 + bom dia 10 
03. Flexora 9 x 6 alternando a carga entre leva e pesado 
1 x 30 curtas + 10 isometria + 12 
1 x unilateral 8 /7/6 até zerar sem intervalo 
04. Flexora em pé 3 x 12 parando no meio + glúteo no cabo 3 x 12 
Panturrilhas sempre 😅
Macacão @santtaloren
.
.
.

✅Horizontal shin angle 
✅Slightly abduct at bottom 
This seems to be something that needs to be stressed often but wide stance anything is not glutes. It is adductors. If you’re “feeling” your glutes working it is your piriformis you’re feeling which is located under the glutes. 

Quads ⬇️
✅Feet low in order to maximize knee flexion 
✅Feet close together 
✅Shins will be more angled, not straight across 

Glutes⬇️
✅Feet high 
✅Feet close together (not as close as quads) 
✅Shin angle will be horizontal 

No matter what your foot position is…
-Keep your lower back/butt on the pad
-Don’t go so deep that you go into posterior pelvic tilt (more ROM isn’t always more effective). If you felt lower back pain from the leg press, this is most likely why. 
-Your feet should remain fully on the pad
.
cc: @daniellewebsterfit

node.text:
UPPER GLUTES 🍑 Visit @SculptMobility for daily pain management, flexibility, and workout advice📚 

 aka glute medius with limited equipment! This was tough!! 🥵👊 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1️⃣ This is THE exercise I would recommend doing if you don’t have the hip abduction chair at your gym! Do it banded to challenge your glutes even more! 12 reps per side x 4

2️⃣ Side walk with a weight plate in your arms and band above your knees. 20 steps per side. Slight bent at your knees! x 3

3️⃣ 7 abductions + 7 hip thrusts equals 1 set. Repeat 3 times. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4️⃣ Lift your leg up, hold 1-2sec, lower it back down and lift it to the side to hold 1-2sec. Repeat 16 reps total x 4. Important to keep a tight core and go slow, control the weight!! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
WHOS UP FOR THE GLUTE BURN?! 😍🔥Song is Kanye West - Follow God
.
.
.
Credit @linnlowes #Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs

node.text: Ladies you NEED to check out @SculptSwim for summers hottest bikinis 👙

FAT BURNER 🔥
.
TAG a friend!

If you’re looking for a quick, killer cardio sesh, give this one a try! This can be done anywhere, anytime! 💪🏼 You can perform this as a circuit or just do each exercise and they’re sets, separately! Either way I promise you’ll feel the burn 🔥 🥵
.
1️⃣ Squat/oblique twist - 4x15
2️⃣ Side jump squat- 3x20
3️⃣ Side lunge/high knee - 4x15 each leg
4️⃣ Squat jump variation - 3x20
.
Credit @ashleigh_jordan #Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs

⠀
Happy Friday IG Fam!! Abs are made in the kitchen but sculpted in the gym. All 10 moves target your entire core. Let me know if you would like more videos like this targeting different areas of the body… TAG A FRIEND who hates trains abs 👀👀
⠀
Credit @chaneldelisser
